{"word":"ἔπαυλος","slug":"ἔπαυλος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἔπαυλος</b></el> <el>(ἔπ-αυλος, ὁ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:αὐλή'><el>αὐλή</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a fold for</i> cattle at night, <el>ἔπαυλοι</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; heterog. <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <el>ἔπαυλα</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>generally, <i>a dwelling, home</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}